      ##What happens if someone gets kicked out of our league for any reason (suspected collusion, continuous non-payment of a team over the salary cap etc).
      After given adequate warnings/communication, if a team needs to be removed from a league for any reason we will notify all owners of that league, suspend that players account and take over that team for the remainder of the season to ensure proper balance and minimal disruption of the league.  We will run the team as we would competitively run our own teams.

      Integrity of our game and league play is essential to us and we will ensure that it is never compromised.

      ##Can I edit our leagues scoring system?
      No, we use a universal scoring system because this allows us to pay out an efficiency grand prize across all leagues.  If different leagues had different scoring systems, this would not be possible  love it

      ##Is there a commissioner in each league?
      No, we do not have a league commissioner assigned in each league because one is not needed.  League settings are all the same across leagues and the trade review process is a league democracy decided by votes.  good

      ##How are trades reviewed?
      Each trade will be reviewed by the teams not involved in the trade to prevent collusion.  If there is a tie in the voting (5-5) the Dynasty Owner review board will rule on if the trade.  We will not prevent trades unless there is obvious collusion.  Andrew and I made it 7 votes needed and they will be charged and then we can review or just make it an automatic rejected trade.  I am open to discussing if it’s automatically rejected or we review it.  With how many times Andrew said trades are contested, it may become cumbersome.

      ##Can there be multiple team trades?
      This year we are only supporting two team trades.  You can trade players for players, players for cap space, players for draft picks or any combination of that, but you can’t do 3+ team trades at this time.  Take out this entire part. It isn’t essential and it doesn’t answer the question.  It just explains what you can trade.  The answer is a direct: Not at this time.  We encourage people to work as creatively as possible within the messaging and league message board to get the best possible trade scenario completed.

      This is a feature we hope to support in coming seasons of Dyansty Owner.

      ##Is this game as awesome as it sounds?
      Yes.

      ##What is the payout annuity and how does it work?
      If you are one of the two teams to play in the dynasty bowl championship game at the end of the year, you will receive a payout that year and for an additional six years for a total of a 7 year payout.   Don’t forget most efficient team gets a payout.  Also, so not to confuse anyone, just say there will be 7 payments made.  We will maket he first annuity payment the year after they win the championship.

      Like when NFL teams reach the Superbowl, there is a long lasting effect on the value of the franchise and we wanted to provide the same element in Dynasty Owner.

      ##What are the penalties for exceeding the salary cap?
      We deviate from the NFL on this in that the NFL has a hard cap where no one can go over that.  We have the same thing, but we have a salary cap that is set below the hard cap and every dollar above the salary cap and up to the hard cap will have a dollar-for-dollar tax applied.  This is the “luxury tax” and it will go towards the Luxury Tax Pot which will be distributed amongst the owners in your league that do not pay any luxury tax and with the Fed

